           If n < SUC x ** r, to show: x ** r <= n
           Let y = ROOT r n ** r.
           Then y <= n                                  by ROOT
            and 2 * HALF (ROOT r n) <= ROOT r n         by TWO_HALF_LESS_EQ
            But x = 2 * HALF (ROOT r n)                 by ROOT_DIV
             so x <= ROOT r n                           by above
             or        x ** r <= y                      by EXP_LE_ISO
           Thus        x ** r <= n                      by LESS_EQ_TRANS

*)
