   Let y = LOG b x, z = LOG b (x ** n).
   Then b ** y <= x /\ x < b ** SUC y              by LOG_THM, (1)
    and b ** z <= x ** n /\ x ** n < b ** SUC z    by LOG_THM, (2)
   From (1),
        b ** (n * y) <= x ** n /\                  by EXP_EXP_LE_MONO, EXP_EXP_MULT
        x ** n < b ** (n * SUC y)                  by EXP_EXP_LT_MONO, EXP_EXP_MULT, 0 < n
