         Then power_index 1 0 = 1         by power_index_of_1
          But k <= 0, so k = 0            by arithmetic
         Hence k <= power_index n m
      If m <> 0,
         Then power_index 1 m = m         by power_index_of_1
         Hence k <= power_index 1 m = m   by given

